New study

The Problemist (published)

Published in: The Problemist 29(9) May 2024.

File: Neuenschwander-2024-TheProblemist-May.pgn

GBR: =0320.88e4f8 FEN: 5k1r/3p2pB/1p1Ppp1p/2p5/2P1KP2/p1P5/P2B1PPP/8 w - - 0 1

1. Bg6 f5+ 2. Ke5! (2. Kd3? h5 3. h4 Rh6 4. g4 Rxg6 5. g5 Ke8! (5 e5? 6. fxe5 Re6 7. f4) 6. Kc2 Kd8 7. Kb3 Kc8 8. Ka4 Kb7 9. Kb5 e5 10. fxe5 Re6 11. f4 Re8 12. Ka4 Ra8+ 13. Kb3 Kc6 14. Bc1 Ra5 15. Bxa3 b5 -/+) 2 h5 3. h4 Rh6 4. g4!! Rxg6 5. g5 Kf7 6. Bc1! Tempo! (6. Be3? Rf6 7. Bxc5 bxc5 8. f3 Kg6 Zugzwang 9. gxf6 gxf6 ) (6. f3? Rf6 7. Be3 Kg6 8. Bf2 Rf8 9. Bxc5 Rc8 -/+) 6 Rf6 7. Be3! (7. Bxa3? Kg6 8. Bc1 Rf8 -/+) 7 Kg6 8. Bxc5! (8. f3? Rf8 9. Bxc5 Rc8 -/+) 8 bxc5 9. f3 Now Black is in Zugzwang 9 Kf7 10. g6+ 1/2-1/2.

Hildebrand +0041.24e7a4 (1945). Cook, correction

Date: 2024, June 7

File: Hildebrand1945a.pgn

In the correction Black wins after 4 Bc8! due to the f-pawn. The study can be corrected by moving the f-pawn to h7.

Terho +0345.46h2a8 (1945). Comment

Source: A.Dunder and A. Hinds, 111 suomalaista Lopputehtv, Suoman Shakki, Jyvskyl, 1946.

Johannes Terho (1885-1961) was a Finnisch chess player and study composer. 46 studies can be found in HHdbVI, of which 35 are original studies by the author; 14 of the 35 studies are cooked (40%). the remaining 11 consist of 10 corrections and one version.

Date: 2024, June 18

File: Terho1945.pgn

Terhos study is incorrect: 5.c5! also wins.

Nf6 Rxf6+) (5. c5! cook BN 5 dxc5 (5 exd5 6. cxd6 cxd6 7. Bxd6) (5 Rg6 6. cxd6 cxd6 7. Bxd6 exd5 8. Ne5) 6. dxe6 Rg6 7. e7 Re6 8. Bxc5) 5 Bxf6 6. dxe6 Rg1 7. Bb4 (7. Ke2? Rg5 8. Hannemann =0011.02b8b3 (1945). Version

Date: 2024, June 18

File: Hannemann1945.pgn

In Hannemanns study, 1. Ne4 is not a cook. The other cooks remain though. My version shows the sacrifice of the white bishop twice (on a4 and a6 in the two mainlines). Either black takes the bishop or the well-known BN-q theoretical draw is reached.

GBR: =0011.02b8b3 FEN: 1K6/8/5N2/8/2p5/1k4p1/8/1B6 w - - 0 1

Tidskrift for Schack=7 Tidskrift for Schack/7. U1 U2: Tidskrift for Schack=10 10/1945 Comment Neuenschwander=B 18/06/2024. 1. Be4 (1. Ne4! cook 1 g2 2. Nd2+ Kb2 3. Nxc4+ Kc1 4. Be4 commnt BN: black is winning! ) 1 c3 2. Ka7 (2. Ka8! cook 2 Ka3 3. Nd5 c2 4. Bxc2 g2 5. Ba4! g1=Q (5 Kxa4 6. Nc3+ Kb3 7. Ne2) 6. Bc6) (2. Nd5! cook 2 g2 3. Bxg2 c2 4. Bf1 c1=Q 5. Ba6) 2 Ka3 (2 Kb2 3. Nd5 c2 4. Nb4) ( 2 Ka2 3. Nd5 c2 4. Nb4+) 3. Ka8 c2 4. Bxc2 g2 5. Be4 g1=Q 6. Bb7 1/2-1/2.
